Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithms for sorting and selection in partially ordered sets (posets), which are fundamental data structures in computer science. The paper also discusses the complexity of these algorithms, which is a key topic in the subfield of computational complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also has applications in ranking and decision-making, which are topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and learning theory (cs.LG). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
